Rule Learning, Theory. 

Rule Learning is present in the text as the paper discusses deductively learned knowledge and how it can be harmful in problem solving. The paper proposes a method called utilization filtering to address this issue. 

Theory is also present in the text as the paper discusses the problem of redundancy in deductive problem solvers and proposes a theoretical solution in the form of utilization filtering. The paper also presents experimental results to support the effectiveness of the proposed approach.
